President Obama has nominated Judge Robert E. Bacharach and Mr. William J. Kayatta, Jr. to the United States Court of Appeals. Judge Bacharach has served as a United States Magistrate Judge on the United States District Court for the Western District of Oklahoma since 1999. He has handled nearly 3,000 civil and criminal matters and has presided over more than 400 judicial settlement conferences. Mr. Kayatta has been a partner at the law firm of Pierce Atwood LLP in Portland, Maine for over 25 years. He has argued two cases to the Supreme Court of the United States and approximately thirty-five cases in state and federal appellate courts. He has also received several awards for his pro bono efforts on behalf of low-income citizens.